Walter Oswald
The scoop of the day
The latest updates
In the post-apocalyptic world
of today, there are many crazy
cults without any rules or laws
that most people would
consider normal. In the first
few years after the failure of
the five main nuclear reactors
due to not being shut down
correctly, there was a
community, aptly named The
Community, created using
genetic modification. The goal
of the community was to serve
as a backup for humanity if
everyone else was killed, as the
people in The Community
have a lower chance of genetic
mutation if exposed to
radiation.
More than a year ago, a high-tech experimental
fighter jet was being tested out, and there was a
malfunction with the navigation system on
board. Due to the malfunction, the pilot
accidentally flew over The Community which
was not his planned flight path, and when he
realized his mistake, he attempted to remedy it
by going back on the same path. By then, it was
already too late, and he was shot down by some
people in The Community. The pilot had
survived the crash, and had radioed for help
multiple times, but help could not arrive fast
enough. The pilot was brutally murdered. Due
to this incident, a new law will be passed to
prevent any future incidents by setting a 20 km
danger zone around The Community.
The plane before it was shot down
New law being passed!
